Sarah Ikumu, a 16-year-old Kenyan living in England, blew the audience away during the recording of 'Showtime At The Apollo', where she performed. Hosted by comedian Steve Harvey, the one-hour weekly show is said to have launched the careers of various legends, including Michael Jackson. Sarah's big debut was on 'Britain's Got Talent', where she was got the golden buzzer and proceeded straight into the semi-final. She finished 7th in the overall performance. However, Simon Powell complimented her and said she was going places. The video of Sarah performing at the Apollo Theatre and getting a standing ovation has gone viral. Tawana: Wow she sounds like Jennifer Hudson! Beautiful voice. Sharon: OH MY GOD!!!! This woman is anointed!!!! She gave me chills and led me into the Holy Spirit...  